Type: Project
Package: data-science-for-biologists-az
Title: R for Biologists — Data Science, Bioinformatics, Machine Learning, Omics, Translatomics, and Single-Cell Analysis in R
Version: 1.0.0
Description: A complete R curriculum for biologists and bioinformaticians covering data wrangling,
    visualization, statistical reasoning, tidymodels-based machine learning, bulk and single-cell
    RNA-seq analysis (DESeq2, Seurat), translatome analysis with anota2seq,
    pathway enrichment, survival analysis with Cox models,
    and reproducible research with renv. Uses real clinical, microarray, translatome,
    and single-cell data.
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends:
    R (>= 4.1)
Imports:
    anota2seq,
    broom,
    DESeq2,
    enrichR,
    fgsea,
    glmnet,
    here,
    knitr,
    limma,
    matrixStats,
    patchwork,
    pheatmap,
    ranger,
    renv,
    rmarkdown,
    scales,
    Seurat,
    survival,
    survminer,
    themis,
    tidymodels,
    tidyverse,
    viridis,
    vip
